AB  - Recently, several hotel chains have begun collaborating with influencers as brand ambassadors. Given the importance and complexity of authenticity in influencer marketing, how people evaluate their authenticity remains unclear. The study sheds light on investigating the effectiveness of virtual and human influencers in facilitating hotel promotions, guided by the core concept of authenticity in tourism, encompassing objective, constructive, existential, and postmodern authenticity. Using data from 311 participants exposed to virtual influencers and 303 participants exposed to human influencers, analysed via SmartPLS, this study confirms that both influencer types effectively promote hotel brands. The four types of authenticity are well-adapted to the influencer marketing context and contribute to hospitality marketing promotions, yet postmodern authenticity does not significantly moderate the relationships among objective, constructive, and existential authenticity. By extending the application of tourism authenticity frameworks to influencer marketing and integrating source credibility theory, this study contributes to a deeper understanding of authenticity in influencer marketing in hospitality and tourism contexts. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
